defaultOne of the major concerns which AIC has, looking forward to some of the targets being discussed o
defaultver the next 30-40 years, is the focus they place on the need for increased production.  Whilst it is imperative that we look forward in that way, and recognise the importance technology will play in that, there is currently a lack of focus on the challeng
defaultes which are placed in the way of the industry accessing technologies.  At a more fundamental level the impact of the hazard to risk issue, raised earlier, 
defaultmeans that industry is also not able to retain existing technology.  AIC is, with the support of oth
defaulter bodies in the agricultural sector, just embarking on project to determine the cumulative impact of threats faced by UK agriculture in the near future whilst at the same time evaluating the opportunities and access to them.  Part of this work has to be a
default fundamental re-evaluation of the legislative decision making processes within the EU system which places a robust scientific assessment at the heart of determining the introduction of new technologies into the EU farming structure.
