defaultthe price spikes of 2008 and a 5.2 per cent rise in the average UK food bill between July 2010 and July 2011
default. 
defaultWhen we think about the sustainability, safety and resilience of UK food imports, we must consider challenges which range from those with a local 
defaultor UK national focus to more wide-ranging European and global issues. These are points highlighted by the Global Food Security Programme (2012).
